<subSubSection id="079E653C537EFFB0FEF386BBFAEDFC59" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="4F3B36B7537EFFB0FEF386BBFAEDFC59" blockId="32.[151,1437,808,1374]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FEF386BBFEF1FC7C" bold="true" box="[199,345,952,978]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Distribution</emphasis>
. Arctic (
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FF8C86BBFD93FC7D" box="[440,571,952,979]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1625" metricValueMax="2.298" metricValueMin="0.027" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1162.5" valueMax="2298.0" valueMin="27.0">27–2298 m</quantity>
), NW Atlantic (3465– 
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FD0486BBFC2FFC7D" box="[816,903,952,979]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.465" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="3465.0">3465 m</quantity>
), NE Atlantic (
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FA1F86BBFB14FC7D" box="[1067,1212,952,979]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.71" metricValueMax="4.813" metricValueMin="0.607" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="2710.0" valueMax="4813.0" valueMin="607.0">607–4813 m</quantity>
), W Atlantic (
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FB6186BBFF47FC59" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0605" metricValueMax="1.067" metricValueMin="1.054" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1060.5" valueMax="1067.0" valueMin="1054.0">1054– 1067 m</quantity>
), E Atlantic (
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FFB786DFFDBCFC59" box="[387,532,988,1015]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.075" metricValueMin="0.425" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1250.0" valueMax="2075.0" valueMin="425.0">425–2075 m</quantity>
), S Africa (
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FCA086DFFC8DFC59" box="[660,805,988,1015]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.579" metricValueMax="2.743" metricValueMin="0.415" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1579.0" valueMax="2743.0" valueMin="415.0">415–2743 m</quantity>
), S 
<collectingCountry id="37937627537EFFB0FD7A86DFFC1DFC58" box="[846,949,988,1014]" name="Australia" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Australia</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FDF086DFFBFDFC59" box="[964,1109,988,1015]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0415" metricValueMax="1.151" metricValueMin="0.932" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1041.5" valueMax="1151.0" valueMin="932.0">932–1151 m</quantity>
). SPA (
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FA9286DFFA91FC59" box="[1190,1337,988,1015]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.375" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.75" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="1375.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="750.0">750–2000 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="079E653C537EFFB0FEF38103FD2EFAF0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4F3B36B7537EFFB0FEF38103FD2EFAF0" blockId="32.[151,1437,808,1374]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FEF38103FE9CFBB4" bold="true" box="[199,308,1024,1050]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Remarks</emphasis>
. A phylogeographical study of mitochondrial COI DNA (
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B46537EFFB0FD808103FB20FBB4" author="O'Hara, T. D. &amp; England, P. R. &amp; Gunasekera, R. &amp; Naughton, K. M." box="[948,1160,1024,1050]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="18 - 28" refId="ref34816" refString="O'Hara, T. D., England, P. R., Gunasekera, R. &amp; Naughton, K. M. (2014) Limited phylogeographic structure for five bathyal ophiuroids at continental scales. Deep Sea Research Part I: Oceanographic Research Papers, 84, 18 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. dsr. 2013.09.009" type="journal article" year="2014">
O’Hara 
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FA248102FBE0FBB4" box="[1040,1096,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
) showed that the species previously identified as 
<taxonomicName id="88844D34537EFFB0FF878127FD09FB90" baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[435,673,1060,1086]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="abyssicola">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FF878127FD09FB90" box="[435,673,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ophiactis abyssicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
contained three separate species-level taxa. 
<taxonomicName id="88844D34537EFFB0FA9A8127FA34FB90" baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[1198,1436,1060,1086]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="abyssicola">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FA9A8127FA34FB90" box="[1198,1436,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ophiactis abyssicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurred throughout the Atlantic from the Arctic to 
<collectingCountry id="37937627537EFFB0FCF9814BFCF2FBCC" box="[717,858,1096,1122]" name="South Africa" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and around as far as the Atlantis seamount (
<geoCoordinate id="2AB05070537EFFB0FB0E814BFA30FBCC" box="[1338,1432,1096,1122]" degrees="32.71" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" precision="555" value="-32.71">32.71°S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="2AB05070537EFFB0FEA3816FFF5CFB29" box="[151,244,1132,1159]" degrees="57.24" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" precision="555" value="57.24">57.24°E</geoCoordinate>
) on the SW Indian Ocean Ridge. 
<taxonomicName id="88844D34537EFFB0FCB7816FFBA0FB28" authority="Lyman, 1879" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1879" box="[643,1032,1132,1159]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FCB7816FFCCFFB28" box="[643,871,1132,1158]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ophiactis cuspidata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B46537EFFB0FD45816EFBA0FB28" author="Lyman, T." box="[881,1032,1132,1159]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="17 - 83" refId="ref33210" refString="Lyman, T. (1879) Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae of the exploring voyage of H. M. S. Challenger under Prof. Sir Wyville Thomson, F. R. S. Part 2. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University, 6, 17 - 83, pls. 11 - 19." type="journal article" year="1879">Lyman, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(here recognised as a full species) occurred around SE Australia, 
<collectingCountry id="37937627537EFFB0FFC58192FD2FFB04" box="[497,647,1168,1195]" name="New Zealand" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
and the Macquarie Ridge in depths of 
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FA088193FB64FB05" box="[1084,1228,1168,1195]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="17.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="950.0" valueMax="1700.0" valueMin="200.0">200–1700 m</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName id="88844D34537EFFB0FAE38193FEEDFB60" authority="Koehler, 1922 b" authorityName="Koehler" authorityYear="1922" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="amator">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FAE38193FA34FB04" box="[1239,1436,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Ophiactis amator</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B46537EFFB0FEA381B7FEEDFB60" author="Koehler, R." box="[151,325,1204,1230]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref32578" refString="Koehler, R. (1922 b) Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea. Scientific Reports. Australasian Antarctic Expedition, Series C, 8 (2), 1 - 98, pls. 76 - 90." type="journal article" year="1922">Koehler, 1922b</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
occurred at depths of ~ 
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FC7B81B7FD44FB61" box="[591,748,1204,1231]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="2850.0" valueMax="4000.0" valueMin="1700.0">1700–4000 m</quantity>
off Southern 
<collectingCountry id="37937627537EFFB0FDB281B7FC45FB60" box="[902,1005,1204,1230]" name="Australia" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="37937627537EFFB0FA1081B6FB16FB60" box="[1060,1214,1204,1231]" name="New Zealand" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. Lower bathyal and abyssal (&gt; 
<quantity id="887C9B52537EFFB0FF3C81DBFEC9FB5D" box="[264,353,1240,1267]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="m" value="2000.0">2000 m</quantity>
) specimens were not sequenced from the Atlantic or 
<collectingCountry id="37937627537EFFB0FD8F81DBFBE2FB5C" box="[955,1098,1240,1266]" name="South Africa" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">South Africa</collectingCountry>
and so it is unclear whether a separate deep-water species occurs there (for which the name 
<taxonomicName id="88844D34537EFFB0FD6781FFFBCEFAB8" authority="Lyman, 1879" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1879" box="[851,1126,1276,1303]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="canotia">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FD6781FFFC62FAB8" box="[851,970,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">O. canotia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2B154B46537EFFB0FDE681FEFBCEFAB8" author="Lyman, T." box="[978,1126,1276,1303]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="17 - 83" refId="ref33210" refString="Lyman, T. (1879) Ophiuridae and Astrophytidae of the exploring voyage of H. M. S. Challenger under Prof. Sir Wyville Thomson, F. R. S. Part 2. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology, Harvard University, 6, 17 - 83, pls. 11 - 19." type="journal article" year="1879">Lyman, 1879</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is available). Here the SPA population is assumed to be 
<taxonomicName id="88844D34537EFFB0FFE78023FDC3FA94" baseAuthorityName="M. Sars" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[467,619,1312,1338]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="abyssicola">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FFE78023FDC3FA94" box="[467,619,1312,1338]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">O. abyssicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its relative proximity to the Atlantis Bank compared to the nearest population of 
<taxonomicName id="88844D34537EFFB0FF008047FE6BFAF0" authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1879" box="[308,451,1348,1374]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiactidae" genus="Ophiactis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphilepidida" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis id="7DF0EAA5537EFFB0FF008047FE6BFAF0" box="[308,451,1348,1374]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">O. cuspidata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
off SE Australia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
